Measure number: In this table, "." or '#DIV/0!' indicates a value cannot be calculated due to a denominator of 0.
External Link: National Performance or Compliance Standard (column H): 4-S1, 4-S2, and 4-P1 through 4-P5 are CFSR4 National Performance values. For details, please see CFSR Technical Bulletin 13A.
Most recent performance (column G): Participation Rates (PR1-PR5), 4-P5: rate per 1,000; 4-S1: rate per 100,000; all others: percentage (%).

Most recent performance relative to standard (national performance / compliance standard) (column I) = (standard)/(num/denom)*100% for measures with desired decrease, '>100' indicates performance of 0, which exceeds standard, but cannot be calculated due to 0 denom; (num/denom)/(standard)*100% for measures with desired increase.

Desired direction (columns J and M): Chevron pointing up ('greater than' symbol) indicates desired increase; pointing down ('less than') indicates desired decrease; x indicates desired direction not established.

Actual one-year and five-year directions (columns K and N): Chevron pointing up ('greater than' symbol) indicates increase; pointing down ('less than') indicates decrease; x indicates one or both values are unavailable and direction of change cannot be calculated. Some items may indicate change not in the desired direction, though percent change (column S) indicates 0.0%. This is due to a change not displayed at one decimal place.
Actual one-year and five-year percent changes (columns L and O) = ((comparison n/comparison d)/(baseline n/baseline d)-1)*100%.
Values between 1 and 10 and calculations based on values between 1 and 10 are masked (***) to protect privacy. In some cases, values >10 may be masked to prevent calculation of small cells.

Measure 8A data (rows 46 through 49) are available from Quarter 2, 2015 onwards. Measure 8A reporting in these workbooks differs from other public 8A data. It is organized by Regional Training Academy groupings rather than CWS/CMS Regional User Groups and quarters rather than Federal Fiscal Years.
